{
  "texts": [
    "The thematic development of keywords from 2000 to 2024 is examined using the keyword thematic map and Sankey diagram presented in Fig. 9.",
    "Analysis of these visualizations reveals that between 2000 and 2021, research primarily concentrated on using computer-aided diagnostics for identifying and categorizing malignancies, particularly breast cancer.",
    "In contrast, the past two years have seen a shift towards leveraging artificial intelligence and support vector machines, significantly enhancing early breast cancer detection and prognosis.",
    "Analysis of co-citation is a pivotal method in bibliometrics for identifying relationships between nodes that represent authors or documents, thus illustrating the intellectual structure of a specific research field [19].",
    "This technique involves recognizing the co-citation of two papers or authors when both are cited by a third entity."
  ]
}